Add missing QHash/QMap includes to base/http/types.h for newer Qt 6.

qBittorrent 4.6.x's src/base/http/types.h uses QMap (Http::HeaderMap) and
QHash for its struct fields but relies on those full definitions being pulled
in transitively. Qt 6.4+ ships only forward declarations via qcontainerfwd.h,
so the build fails with "field ... has incomplete type 'QMap<QString,QString>'".
This is the same defect already patched on the 4.4 and 4.5 lines; see
qbittorrent-4.4-qt6-headers.patch and qbittorrent-4.5-qt6-headers.patch.

--- a/src/base/http/types.h
+++ b/src/base/http/types.h
@@ -29,7 +29,9 @@

 #pragma once

+#include <QHash>
 #include <QHostAddress>
+#include <QMap>
 #include <QString>
 #include <QVector>
